    {
        "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1775463102.486289",
        "client_msg_id": "b2648ff6-3fdb-4b87-9a80-9972e1401913",
        "text": "yeah the self-triggering loops are the bane of my existence.\n\n<@UEH6T3RJB> claims to have solved bi-direcitonal reactivity in `fluid.cell` <https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/post\/2026-02-20-reactivity-for-malleability\/>\n\nI am still trying to get my head around it.\n\nYour approach is interesting. I feel like there is this modernist approach to coding where we build fragile mathematical towers, a topological sort being a great example of.\nThen there is the post-modernist approach, where we wire into systems we can't understand (e.g. a user's randomly configured operating system) and then apply techniques to deal with the chaos, which inhibition would be more like. The post-modern can end up more robust and fault tolerant, but ultimately even harder to reason about because its adding more entropy on top of the existing entropy.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "27dffd0e73bd",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2021-09-13\/2483463922595_27dffd0e73bd6f709927_72.gif",
            "first_name": "Tom",
            "real_name": "Tom Larkworthy",
            "display_name": "Tom Larkworthy",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "tom.larkworthy",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1775053630.907069",
        "parent_user_id": "U06SS0DHZD1",
        "attachments": [
            {
                "image_url": "https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/img\/pond.jpg",
                "image_width": 500,
                "image_height": 375,
                "image_bytes": 132630,
                "from_url": "https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/post\/2026-02-20-reactivity-for-malleability\/",
                "id": 1,
                "original_url": "https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/post\/2026-02-20-reactivity-for-malleability\/",
                "fallback": "Antranig Basman: fluid.cell: A reactive implementation supporting malleable substrates",
                "title": "fluid.cell: A reactive implementation supporting malleable substrates",
                "title_link": "https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/post\/2026-02-20-reactivity-for-malleability\/",
                "service_name": "Antranig Basman"
            }
        ],
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "O4scw",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "yeah the self-triggering loops are the bane of my existence.\n\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "UEH6T3RJB"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " claims to have solved bi-direcitonal reactivity in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "fluid.cell",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/ponder.org.uk\/post\/2026-02-20-reactivity-for-malleability\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nI am still trying to get my head around it.\n\nYour approach is interesting. I feel like there is this modernist approach to coding where we build fragile mathematical towers, a topological sort being a great example of.\nThen there is the post-modernist approach, where we wire into systems we can't understand (e.g. a user's randomly configured operating system) and then apply techniques to deal with the chaos, which inhibition would be more like. The post-modern can end up more robust and fault tolerant, but ultimately even harder to reason about because its adding more entropy on top of the existing entropy."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "reactions": [
            {
                "name": "eyes",
                "users": [
                    "U05UK5T7LPP"
                ],
                "count": 1
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "text": "The easter holidays I got sick and vibe coded a\n\n*RISC-V Linux BusyBox Single Board Computer*\n<https:\/\/tomlarkworthy.github.io\/lopebooks\/notebooks\/@tomlarkworthy_linux-sbc.html>\n\nin a single HTML file. Its quite different to Fabrice's jslinux, it is a JS emulator of the Risk V instruction set, rather than a WASM emscripten toolchain approach.\n\nI wanted to understand the linux boot process. Vibed with my new Claude code plugin for notebooks which is incredibly productive albeit still with a fair few rough edges.",
